<MudContainer MaxWidth="@MaxWidth.Large">
    <CHPostHeader PostInfo="@PostInfo" />
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.h3">
        Disclaimer!
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        This documentation assumes you have legally aquired the game files from your own arcade machine! As a reminder: Do not distribute your game files to other people. Continue supporting local arcades!
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        This also assumes you're computer is running Windows. I'm unaware of a way to do this on other operating systems.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.h3">
        How To Get The Game Running
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="1." />Download spice2x from <MudLink Href="https://github.com/spice2x/spice2x.github.io/releases" Target="_blank">https://github.com/spice2x/spice2x.github.io/releases</MudLink>.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="2." />Configure Spice.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="1" /><CHTextBullet />Copy "spice.exe" (the non-64-bit version!) and "spicecfg.exe" to the "contents" directory of the game.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="1" /><CHTextBullet />Run Spice Config ("spicecfg.exe").
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="2" /><CHTextBullet />Go to the "Options" tab.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="2" /><CHTextBullet />Enable "Basic Local EA Emulation".
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="2" /><CHTextBullet />Assign "PCBID" to <CHCodeInline>00010203040506070809</CHCodeInline>.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="4." />Attempt to run the game by starting Spice ("spice.exe").
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="1" /><CHTextBullet />You may crash from an access violation after the log "M:ddr: Renderer:initGs() end."
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="2" /><CHTextBullet />If so, you need to install Direct X. Download link: <MudLink Href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=35" Target="_blank">https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=35</MudLink>.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="5." />Download and install a K-Lite Codec Pack from <MudLink Href="https://codecguide.com/download_kl.htm" Target="_blank">https://codecguide.com/download_kl.htm</MudLink>. This is for the game to be able to play the music videos.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="1" /><CHTextBullet />I got the "Standard" pack so I can also have fun looking at the game files but you only need the "Basic" pack for the videos to work in-game.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.h3">
        Extra Steps
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        Tip: Spice's "Coin Mech" button doesn't seem to do anything to the credits/coins in-game. You can use the "Service" input instead to add coins.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        How to enable English (or other languages) by default.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="1." />Open the game's test menu (via the "Test" input).
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="2." />Enter "GAME OPTIONS".
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="3." />Assign "LANGUAGE SETTING" to "English".
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="1" /><CHTextBullet />Use "Service" input to shift through the choices.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        You might be interested in setting a few other options as well in the test menu.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        Changing the required coins per credit.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />Assign "COIN SLOT" to "1 COIN&nbsp&nbsp1 CREDIT" (or another value).
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.h3">
        Using Patches (And Tweaking Latency!)
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        Patches are like "cheats" (similar to Gecko codes for the Wii/GameCube). These are necessary for enabling and configuring certain features of the offline game.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="1." />Open your game's Spice Config and go to the "Patches" tab.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="2." />Enable "Auto apply patches on game start" (unless you want to permanently modify the game files for some reason).
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="3." />Hit "Import from URL" and enter <CHCodeInline><MudLink Href="https://sp2x.two-torial.xyz/" Target="_blank" Color="@Color.Inherit">https://sp2x.two-torial.xyz/</MudLink></CHCodeInline>.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet BulletString="4." />Enable the desired patches.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        Patches I use:
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />"Song Unlock"
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />"Unlock options"
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />"SSQ Offset" or a combination of "Render Offset" and "Sound Offset".
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="1" /><CHTextBullet />Set these offsets to the latency of your TV and/or speakers.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.h3">
        Additional Notes
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        Windowed mode is helpful for being able to alt-tab out and back in while testing the game. During fullscreen, the game seems to break if window focus is taken away. Fullscreen is definitely worth it when you actually want to play though! Runs way faster.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        When configuring inputs, prefer using "naive" bindings over raw device input bindings. Raw device input bindings are prone to changing when devices are added or removed, requiring you to reconfigure them again.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        My current choice for key bindings:
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />P1 menu arrows: WASD.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />P1 start: Left shift.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />P2 menu arrows: Arrow keys.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />P2 start: Right shift.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />Test menu: Backtick key (the "tilde" key).
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />Insert coin: Insert key.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />The rationale for using the shift keys for the start buttons is to keep the controls symmetrical between P1 and P2.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <br>
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        Random note: Convenient window positions for a fullscreen-like experience:
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />For 1920x1080: <CHCodeInline>-8,-31</CHCodeInline>.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />For 3840x2160: <CHCodeInline>-16,-62</CHCodeInline>.
    </MudText>
    <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
        <CHTextIndent IndentationLevel="0" /><CHTextBullet />For 2560x1600: <CHCodeInline>-11,-45</CHCodeInline>.
    </MudText>
</MudContainer>

